reviews.text: Old fashion Chinese restaurant. Friendly and the hot pot was excellent. Old copper pot using charcoal. Mongolian fatty mutton was very good. Will go back to try their Beijing dishes

Very disappointing experience. Very expensive for below average food. We went for dinner and had problems finding a good seat even thou we had a reservation. The room is strangely cut so that some tables are not in the main room anymore. Not cozy at all. We had chicken, sour cabbage and dandan noodles. The chicken was reheated and still cold inside when it came and the cabbage was not sour as we were used to it. When coming home we had stomach problems from all the oil... I wouldn’t come back, every wet market has better food for half the price.
Great lunch for a great price $55, select main course, then all u can eat veggies (3 types), soup and rice.
$90 一個飯一個餸，味道一般，半自助涼拌性價比很低，唔會再來食🤦🏻‍♂️
好正，80蚊有主菜一個，飯一碗，另加任食當日四個涼菜，任飲湯同小米粥，正正😝大胃王LIKE
